  "tips": [
    "The Col d'Ibardin is located on the Franco-Spanish border, in the Pyrenees. It separates the department of Pyrénées-Atlantiques, in France, from the foral community of Navarre, in Spain.",
    "Small land \"beach\" on the lake, perfect for taking a break in the shade of the trees and at the water's edge",
    "Incredible 360º views, one of those peaks in the region that go unnoticed due to its shape and modest altitude.",
    "The first section from Biriatou is steep and I had to push the gravel bike a few meters. When the track widens you can ride without any problem."
